commitResults.messageTitle: Implemented Skeletal Structure for Duke
Added functionality to store a dynamic list of strings and read back the list to user
Added Task Class and modified Duke.java to work with Task - Allow easier future modifications
Added 3 new subclasses for Tasks, and modified Task and Duke to work with this three new tasks
Modfied expected and input file for automated tests
Add dukeException class and two exceptions that extends dukeException. Modify Duke.java to handle exceptions thrown.
Add printListNumber function to avoid repeating code. Add functionality to remove items.
Add save functionality to data/duke.txt
Modify Event and Deadline class to use LocalDateTime
Change code style
Modify Event and Deadline classes to work with LocalDateTime
Add Gradle support for ip
Add four new classes and modify Duke to incoporate more OOP
Refactor the classes into seperated classes
Add JUnit tests for Parser and TaskList
Add JavaDocs to almost all classes and methods.
Refactor code to adhere to coding standards.
Add find functionality
Merge and small edit to code standards.
Add GUI to Duke with JavaFX
Tidy code with CheckStyle
Add uses of assert statements.
commitResults.messageBody:
There are several instances whereby Strings and ArrayLists should not be
null, and  useage of assert statements are introduced to guard these
instances.

First usages of assert statements, expect more to come.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code to improve readability.
commitResults.messageBody:
Remove several return statements and have the function return once at
the end of the function. Expect to refactor code due to long parser
functions which will increase with increasingly more commands.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add support for adding and removing expenses.
commitResults.messageBody:
Commands are to be preceded with an "e" and separaters are an "/" before
the cost of the expense.
Example command: e misc macs /30

Current supports misc, food, transport, add, remove, list and storing
and saving from file.
